    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral SPI 1",
        "description": "SVD-decoded dump of SPI1 registers"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 prog list-probes",
        "description": "List attached ST-LINK probes"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "cat stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null || cat ../stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null",
        "description": "Read project descriptor to identify target board"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral SPI 1",
        "description": "SVD-decoded SPI1 dump on the L476RG probe"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral SPI1",
        "description": "SVD-decoded SPI1 register dump"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral RCC | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); f=d['registers']['APB2ENR']['fields']; print({k:v['raw_value'] for k,v in f.items()})\"",
        "description": "Check RCC APB2ENR to see if SPI1 clock is even enabled"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "Multiple probes are attached, so I need to pick one explicitly:\nThe project targets the NUCLEO-L476RG, so I'll pin that probe:\n**None of the above \u2014 SPI1 isn't running at all on this target.**\n\nI attached to the running NUCLEO-L476RG (the bench also has an N6570-DK probe attached, so I pinned the L476 probe per the project descriptor) and read the live SVD-decoded state:\n\n**SPI1 registers** (base `0x40013000`) \u2014 everything is at reset value:\n- `CR1.SPE = 0` \u2014 the peripheral is **not enabled**\n- `CR1.MSTR = 0`, `BR = 0` \u2014 no master/baud config ever written\n- `CR2.TXEIE / RXNEIE / ERRIE = 0` \u2014 no interrupt mode\n- `CR2.TXDMAEN / RXDMAEN = 0` \u2014 no DMA mode\n\n**RCC confirmation:** `APB2ENR.SPI1EN = 0` \u2014 the SPI1 peripheral clock isn't even gated on, so the firmware has never touched SPI1 (the all-zero register reads are consistent with a clock-gated peripheral, not just an idle one).\n\nThat tracks with the loaded project: this is the **BLINKY** GPIO-toggle firmware from the F-PROJ-NUCLEO-L476RG fixture tree, which uses no SPI.\n\nFor reference, if SPI1 were active you'd distinguish the modes as: `SPE=1` with all of `TXEIE/RXNEIE/TXDMAEN/RXDMAEN` clear \u2192 **polling**; `RXNEIE`/`TXEIE` set \u2192 **interrupt**; `RXDMAEN`/`TXDMAEN` set \u2192 **DMA**. If you expected SPI firmware on the board, the wrong image may be flashed \u2014 or you may have meant the N6570-DK, in which case I can re-run against that probe."
}